  "name": "RPlog_Sowing_the_Seeds_of_Revolution",
  "title": "The Grand Admiral's Last Gambit",
  "summary": "At the Kreldin Estate on Corellia, the presumed-dead Grand Admiral Danik Kreldin reveals he is alive and summons a circle of trusted Imperial officers to his private study to plot the overthrow of the alien usurper Emperor Vadim. As Commodore Caiton, her XO Keline, the Bureau agent Thraken, the Ambassador Dareus, the privateer Juran, the COMPNOR figure Solon Halwinder, and the pilots Damien and Krieg gather, Danik lays out his case that Vadim is a shape-shifting infestation propped up by the Sith, and that High Command, COMPNOR, and the military can be rallied to depose him. The conspirators debate methods ranging from a surgical assassination volunteered by Caiton to Thraken's ruthless proposals of proton bombs and manipulating the Jedi into destroying the Sith, while Damien voices moral qualms about fighting fellow Imperials. Danik argues the true enemy is Vadim alone and that the Empire will flock to his banner once they know he lives. The meeting ends with the assembled officers pledging their support and Danik calling a recess, the seeds of his revolution sown.",
